{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b8c7b4e7-4494-4b9f-ab69-253ec40187d9","content":"Here's the mapping from VSTest → Microsoft.Testing.Platform flags:\n\n| VSTest flag | MTP equivalent | Required package |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | *(built-in)* |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` | `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` | *(same package)* |\n\nOn **.NET 8**, `dotnet test` doesn't natively speak MTP, so pass the new flags after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nMake sure your test project also sets `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in its `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`) and references the four NuGet packages listed above.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1971b770-00a4-4e20-945f-2f370f7082e5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling - I can answer this directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me break down their current command and map each flag:\n\nCurrent command:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" --logger trx --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\" --blame-crash --blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m\n```\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the CLI surface changes significantly. The key differences:\n\n\n- `--filter` remains the same for test filtering\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` and requires the Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport package\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` changes to `--coverage` with the Microsoft.CodeCoverage package\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump` via Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout` need to be checked for equivalent support in the new platform\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I can still use `dotnet test` as the entry point, but the arguments get forwarded differently. For .NET 8 specifically, I might need to run the test executable directly or use `dotnet run --project` instead, depending on the SDK version and how the integration is set up.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the equivalent flags between the old `dotnet test` arguments and the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform syntax—things like `--filter` staying the same, but `--logger trx` becoming `--report-trx`, and the blame-related flags transforming into `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` with their respective package dependencies.\n\nFor .NET 8, the practical approach is to pass these arguments after `--` when running the test project, or if using the newer integration available in .NET 9+, the syntax becomes more streamlined. Since .NET 8 doesn't have full built-in support, the best path forward is adding the required NuGet packages and either running the project directly or using the MSBuild bridge for better integration.","outputTokens":1296,"requestId":"3413:386D1F:560BCF6:5E2D576:69F3FAFF"},"id":"499657e8-8666-4292-9017-f82de93d1014","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:07.751Z","parentId":"20597843-acb3-452a-81f4-56ac92b6c522"}
